@Node INFORMATION "Yamaha QS300 Voices - Information"
@{bpen 1}@{FG shine}@{b}Distribution@{ub}                                                                         ***@{FG text}@{bpen 0}
 This guide has been released as an public document. You are free to post it or send it
wherever you want as long as credit for the work remains with myself. In addition, if
you want to include this guide on any software-collection (CD-Roms etc), you should ask
for permission first.

@{bpen 1}@{FG shine}@{b}Introduction@{ub}                                                                         ***@{FG text}@{bpen 0}
 This guide is designed as a ultimate reference for those musicians who own the Yamaha
QS-300 Workstation. It was written by me, but includes information from many sources,
most importantly the manuals and inlayed sheets from voice-disks.
 Because I'm a proud OctaMED Soundstudio user and I'm using my QS-300 with lots of sets
full of different voices (each set consists of 128 sounds), I naturally needed an @{"index" link INDEX}
of those voices available in my storage. Because of the Soundstudio's launching external
programs possibility this idea went me to make an file in amiga-guide format for easy
use. Later (after it was finished) I've decided to upload this file into Aminet-sites,
because I assume someone could enjoy it -> If you find this useful, contact me !
 I have tried my best to ensure all information contained is correct. However I do not
take responsibility for any incorrect information (if so, let me know).
 I hope to be able to continue updating this for as long as I own my QS-300.

