@{bpen 1}@{FG shine}@{b}Hardware utilized:@{ub}                                                                   ***@{FG text}@{bpen 0}
 AmigaTech A1200T Computer @{i}(68040/40,32MB Edo-Fast RAM,NEC 16x CD-Rom)@{ui}
 AmigaTech M1438S Autoscan Monitor @{i}(Super 72:800x600,83Hz,27.262kHz)@{ui}
 Yamaha QS-300 Workstation

@{bpen 1}@{FG shine}@{b}History@{ub}                                                                              ***@{FG text}@{bpen 0}
@{b}Version 1.4 @{ub} (Internal release, 26th January 1998)
 Active @{i}Contents@{ui} button everywhere + full @{i}Index@{ui} support
 Contains QS300 specification part in @{i}Specs@{ui} section
 @{i}About@{ui} section moved into @{i}Information@{ui} section
 Added self-made guide icon 
@{b}Version 1.3 @{ub} (Aminet release, 08th January 1998)
 Added index of @{u}XG Voices@{uu}
 Voice indexes now as separate add files in @{i}Adds@{ui} directory (for smaller memory usage)
 Totally 19 voice sets and 2563 voices inside !
@{b}Version 1.2 @{ub} (Internal release, 02nd January 1998)
 Added @{u}Synsations@{uu} and @{u}Vintage@{uu} voice sets
 Several layout changes as you can see
@{b}Version 1.1 @{ub} (Internal release, 28th December 1997)
 Added @{u}Public@{uu} voice set
 Added History part in @{i}Information@{ui} section
@{b}Version 1.0 @{ub} (Aminet release, 27th October 1997)
 First public release
 Added @{u}Dance@{uu}, @{u}Xtasy@{uu}, @{u}Power Generator@{uu} and @{u}Trippy@{uu} voice sets
@{b}Version 0.9 @{ub} (Internal release, 15th September 1997)
 Initial non-public release
 Contains @{u}Preset@{uu}, @{u}Factory@{uu}, @{u}Dance Machine@{uu} & @{u}Rave Style@{uu}, @{u}Hit Factory@{uu}, @{u}SFX@{uu} and @{u}Synth Heaven@{uu}
  voice sets
 Contains @{i}Notes@{ui} section for better shortcut-orientation
@EndNode

@Node NOTES "Yamaha QS300 Voices - Notes"
